<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Finding 2 · Client-Side Trust</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/learn.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="learn-page">
    <div class="brand brand-sm" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
      <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
      <span>CySER Workshop · Skyway engagement</span>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-hero">
      <div class="hero-icon">🍪</div>
      <h1>Finding 2 confirmed</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Day 2 · Client-Side Trust / Cookie Tampering</p>
      <div class="flag-badge"><%= flag %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-grid">
      <div class="learn-card skill-card">
        <div class="card-icon">📚</div>
        <h2>The vulnerability</h2>
        <h3>Trusting user-controlled state</h3>
        <p>Cookies, hidden form fields, JS variables, URL parameters. Anything the client can write is anything the client can <em>rewrite</em>. Gating authorization on "what the cookie says" is gating it on the attacker's preferences.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card world-card">
        <div class="card-icon">📰</div>
        <h2>Seen in the wild</h2>
        <h3>"is_admin = true"</h3>
        <p>Real apps have shipped this. Travel sites have priced premium economy as economy because of a client-side fare cookie. E-commerce sites have applied $0 totals because of a checkout cookie the user could edit. Privilege levels have escalated through one base64-decode-and-edit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card career-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🛠️</div>
        <h2>How to fix it</h2>
        <h3>Server is the source of truth</h3>
        <p>Look up the user's tier in your database on every privileged request. If you must put state in a cookie, sign it (HMAC) and verify the signature server-side. Treat cookie contents as adversarial input.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card key-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔑</div>
        <h2>One-line takeaway</h2>
        <h3>Never trust the client</h3>
        <p>Authentication says <em>who</em>; authorization says <em>what they can do</em>. Both checks belong on the server, every request, no exceptions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-nav">
      <a href="/" class="nav-btn secondary">← All findings</a>
      <% if (hasNext) { %><a href="/challenge/<%= nextNum %>" class="nav-btn primary">Day <%= nextNum %> →</a><% } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
